<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Brisbane's most connected address.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Brisbane CBD and its surrounding precincts attract a broad range of buyers, from owner-occupiers seeking walkable city living to investors drawn by yield and capital growth. Understanding that buyer mix is critical to a successful campaign.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      With deep knowledge of Brisbane's inner city and a wide buyer network through Ray White Bulimba, I can position your property to attract the right buyers and generate genuine competition.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The 2032 Olympics is acting as a once-in-a-generation catalyst for Brisbane CBD apartment values, with government investment in venues, transport and public realm raising the city's international profile significantly. Queen Street Mall and the surrounding George and Albert Street precincts continue to evolve as urban living destinations, with new mixed-use towers bringing residential density that is supporting rental yields well above other capital cities. Owner-occupier interest in high-quality CBD apartments has grown as remote work flexibility makes CBD living more attractive to professionals who previously commuted from outer suburbs. Strong interstate demand from Melbourne and Sydney buyers seeking better value per square metre continues to underpin CBD sales activity.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">CBD Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner-city Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">High Demand</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Strong buyer pipeline</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/new-farm" style="color:#c4912a;">New Farm</a>, <a href="/suburbs/fortitude-valley" style="color:#c4912a;">Fortitude Valley</a>, <a href="/suburbs/kangaroo-point" style="color:#c4912a;">Kangaroo Point</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

