        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Brisbane CBD continues to see strong rental demand from professionals, international students and short-stay tenants ahead of the 2032 Olympics. Vacancy rates have remained low, supporting investor confidence in the precinct.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is buying in Brisbane CBD a good investment right now?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">CBD apartments offer attractive rental yields compared to houses in the inner east, and upcoming infrastructure investment tied to the 2032 Games is expected to support ongoing demand. Buyers should assess body corporate costs, building age and supply levels in their chosen precinct carefully.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

